\ul b. Pitch usage\ulnone \
Again, we would expect to see at least some hierarchy reflecting the key profile. For illustration, see the image \'92C major fugue histogram\'92 in which the key notes (C, D, E, F, G, A, B) are used more than the others. As we discussed, for a larger corpus we might see a hierarchy on a greater number of levels, assuming that we\'92ve compared like with like (normalised for key, and separated major from minor chorales).\
